### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api/v1
@authToken = Bearer REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN
@filename = REPLACE_WITH_UPLOADED_FILENAME.webp

### Upload Image - Success (requires auth)
# Note: Replace the file path below with a real local image path in your repo/machine.
# Example: < ./api/tests/http/assets/sample.png (create this file if it doesn't exist)
POST {{baseUrl}}/images
Authorization: {{authToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary123

--boundary123
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="image"; filename="sample.png"
Content-Type: image/png

< ./api/tests/http/assets/sample.png
--boundary123--

### Upload Image - Missing file (requires auth)
POST {{baseUrl}}/images
Authorization: {{authToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=boundary123

--boundary123--

### Get Image - Auth required
# Replace the filename variable with the value returned from the upload response (data.filename)
GET {{baseUrl}}/images/{{filename}}
Authorization: {{authToken}}

### Get Image - Unauthorized
GET {{baseUrl}}/images/{{filename}}
